<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-11177] CoAP component starts redundant server instance</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-11177</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If I configure a simple camel-coap consumer endpoint like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;from(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;coap:&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//localhost:8080/foo&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Logging reveals that two server instances were started:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;[org.eclipse.californium.core.network.CoapEndpoint] (pool-3-thread-1) Stopping endpoint at address 0.0.0.0/0.0.0.0:52697
[org.eclipse.californium.core.network.CoapEndpoint] (pool-3-thread-1) Stopping endpoint at address 0.0.0.0/0.0.0.0:8080 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/blob/master/components/camel-coap/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/coap/CoAPComponent.java#L148-L153&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;This&lt;/a&gt; appears to be the logic that causes the behaviour. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do we need it? It seems to be a duplicate of what already happens in &lt;tt&gt;createConsumer()&lt;/tt&gt;. Also, the creation of a default server can easily be done in the &lt;tt&gt;createServer()&lt;/tt&gt; method, I don&apos;t think we need it in &lt;tt&gt;doStart()&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
